org.webcat.reporter.datamodel
Interface IResultSet

public interface IResultSet

Represents the results of a query on the Web-CAT data store. A row in the result set corresponds to values of the set of variables in a query. Data can be read from the result set by evaluating key paths starting at one of these variables.

Author:
Tony Allowatt

Method Detail

moveToFirstRow

boolean moveToFirstRow()
Moves the current position of the result set to the first row.

Returns:
true if the current position was able to be moved to the first row; otherwise, false (that is, if the result set contained no rows).

moveToNextRow

boolean moveToNextRow()
Moves the current position to the next row in the result set, if the next row exists.

Returns:
true if the current position was able to be moved; otherwise, false if the current position is already at the last row.

moveToRow

boolean moveToRow(int row)

Moves the current position to a specific row in the result set.

This is a linear-time operation, since moving to the ith row requires the current position to be reset to the first row and then moved row-by-row to the ith position.

Parameters:
row - the 0-based index of the row to move to.
Returns:
true if the current position was able to be moved; otherwise, false if the specified position is after the last row in the result set.

currentRow

int currentRow()
Returns the index of the current row the cursor is on in the result set.

Returns:
the 0-based index of the current row.

hasNextRow

boolean hasNextRow()
Returns a value indicating whether there are more rows available in the result set.

Returns:
true if there are more rows available; otherwise, false if the current position is at the last row.

wasNull

boolean wasNull()
Returns a value indicating whether the last xxxValueForKeyPath call was null or invalid.

Returns:
true if the last xxxValueForKeyPath call was null; otherwise, false.

valueForKeyPath

Object valueForKeyPath(String keyPath)

Retrieves the value of the specified key path in the result set as a generic object, without performing any data conversion.

If you need to evaluate a key path whose type is a primitive value (such as an integer or floating-point value), you should use one of the specialized xxxValueForKeyPath methods provided so that some basic String-to-value conversion can be performed if needed (this is the case when a key path has its destination in a plain-text Java properties file, where all values are Strings).

Parameters:
keyPath - the key path to be evaluated
Returns:
the value of the key path

stringValueForKeyPath

String stringValueForKeyPath(String keyPath)

Retrieves the string value of the specified key path in the result set.

This method calls valueForKeyPath(keyPath) and then returns the result of calling the toString() method on that object.

Parameters:
keyPath - the key path to be evaluated
Returns:
the string value of the key path

booleanValueForKeyPath

boolean booleanValueForKeyPath(String keyPath)

Retrieves the boolean value of the specified key path in the result set.

This method tries the following operations to get a boolean value for the key path:

  1. Call valueForKeyPath(keyPath).
  2. If the result is of type Boolean, cast it and return the result of Boolean.booleanValue().
  3. Otherwise, call toString() on the raw object and then attempt to parse that with Boolean.parseBoolean.
  4. If parsing succeeds, return the result. If it fails, the return value is undefined and wasNull is set to true.

Parameters:
keyPath - the key path to be evaluated
Returns:
the boolean value of the key path

charValueForKeyPath

char charValueForKeyPath(String keyPath)

Retrieves the character value of the specified key path in the result set.

This method tries the following operations to get a character value for the key path:

  1. Call valueForKeyPath(keyPath).
  2. If the result is of type Character, cast it and return the result of Character.charValue().
  3. Otherwise, call toString() on the raw object. If the resulting String has length 1, return the sole character in the String. If the String has more than one character, the return value is undefined and wasNull is set to true.

Parameters:
keyPath - the key path to be evaluated
Returns:
the character value of the key path

dateValueForKeyPath

Date dateValueForKeyPath(String keyPath)

Retrieves the date value of the specified key path in the result set.

This method tries the following operations to get a Date value for the key path:

  1. Call valueForKeyPath(keyPath).
  2. If the result is of type Date, return it.
  3. Otherwise, call toString() on the raw object and then attempt to parse that with NSTimestampFormatter.parseObjectInUTC, using the default date format pattern.
  4. If parsing succeeds, return the result. If it fails, the return value is undefined and wasNull is set to true.

Parameters:
keyPath - the key path to be retrieved
Returns:
the java.util.Date value of the key path
